---
// BETA — "Why this exists" prose section. Blueprint-blue-gray on warm parchment.
---
<section class="bg-eai-parchment text-eai-blueprint">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-20 md:py-24">
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-5">
      Why this exists
    </p>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none font-serif text-eai-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        The 240-year school-trust record is the only multi-generational fiduciary
        experiment large enough, public enough, and old enough to teach us how
        the architecture of long-horizon obligation breaks.
      </p>
      <p>
        The same failure modes recur across states and centuries:
        <span class="font-sans text-base text-eai-blueprint">
          weak fiduciary duty, missing restoration mechanisms, no legal defense,
          no trustee education, no standing civic community.
        </span>
        The pattern is structural, not accidental.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Eighth Anchor Institute applies these lessons to the next generation
        of intergenerational trusts now being designed — AI governance,
        climate adaptation, treaty obligations, endowments, sovereign wealth.
        The discipline begins with the record we already have.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
